title: Bruin Actuarial Society Case Competition
description:
This case competition tasked myself along with my 3 fellow team members to conduct an insurance portfolio analysis for a realty company. 
                    We were given data on the accident history for the estate assets held by this company. 
                    Using this information we were able to run a Monte Carlo Simulation to conduct a stress test on each insurance option, 
                    which allowed us to determine which option best satisfied our client's needs
                    To view our presentation as well as the other finalists click here.
